\taxon{Definition}
\title{Zariski topology}
\import{macro}

\p{
  The \em{Zariski topology} on #{\spec D} is induced by a basis #{O_p} for each #{p\in D},
  ##{ O_p := \scomp{x\in \spec D}{p \in x}. }
  It is easy to verify that
  ##{ O_1 = \spec D, \quad O_0 = \emptyset, \quad O_{p \wedge q} = O_p \cap O_q, \quad O_{p \vee q} = O_p \cup O_q,}
  thus this indeed forms a basis.
}